          "notes": "The module is technically rigorous and well-structured, with real-world case studies (Notion, Slack AI, Intercom Fin) that ground abstract concepts convincingly, and quiz questions that genuinely test judgment rather than recall. The primary weakness is in lab executability: the chat-based labs depend on an AI assistant backend that is not shown to be configured or available, the lab instructions lack explicit success criteria or completion rubrics, and there is no fallback for learners who cannot access a live API \u2014 making D5/C1 the most fragile element. Narrative functions more as contextual framing than true discovery-driven storytelling, so learner insight-arrival (D1/C2) is adequate but not guided.",
          "topIssue": "Lab executability is the critical gap: the chat labs assume a connected AI backend with no fallback, no explicit completion criteria, and no way for learners to self-assess whether their design discussions met the learning objective \u2014 add a structured checklist or offline reflection prompt so the lab has value even without a live API connection.",
